1
00:01:33,326 --> 00:01:34,027
Professor Jiang.

2
00:01:35,528 --> 00:01:36,029
I'm sorry.

3
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:41,034
Director Zhou.

4
00:01:42,469 --> 00:01:43,636
Hearing you say that

5
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:46,906
is enough for me.

6
00:01:51,010 --> 00:01:53,913
I can withdraw the lawsuit too.

7
00:01:56,983 --> 00:01:57,884
Being a doctor

8
00:01:58,585 --> 00:01:59,352
isn't easy, is it?

9
00:02:00,153 --> 00:02:02,789
Especially when you're trying to be a good one.

10
00:02:04,157 --> 00:02:04,958
It really isn't.

11
00:02:08,428 --> 00:02:09,829
But it was never supposed to be easy.

12
00:02:12,432 --> 00:02:13,366
Every day,

13
00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:15,602
we face matters of life and death.

14
00:02:18,037 --> 00:02:19,405
We should be cautious

15
00:02:20,006 --> 00:02:20,707
and tread carefully.

16
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:27,313
How about you?

17
00:02:28,014 --> 00:02:28,815
How have you been lately?

18
00:02:29,549 --> 00:02:30,984
I recently completed

19
00:02:31,084 --> 00:02:32,152
my retirement paperwork.

20
00:02:33,453 --> 00:02:35,121
After teaching all my life,

21
00:02:35,388 --> 00:02:36,389
suddenly having nothing to do

22
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:38,158
takes some getting used to.

23
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:40,960
When I'm home alone,

24
00:02:41,361 --> 00:02:42,095
I often think back

25
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,530
to my time in the hospital.

26
00:02:44,931 --> 00:02:46,065
Whenever I think of children like Du Yan

27
00:02:46,132 --> 00:02:47,200
who have to wait so long

28
00:02:47,433 --> 00:02:48,735
for a donor,

29
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:51,271
my heart aches.

30
00:02:52,038 --> 00:02:54,040
So I made a decision.

31
00:02:54,707 --> 00:02:55,842
After I pass away,

32
00:02:56,075 --> 00:02:57,443
I'll donate my organs and body

33
00:02:57,844 --> 00:02:59,078
for medical use.

34
00:03:01,881 --> 00:03:03,516
Rather than being cremated into ashes

35
00:03:03,583 --> 00:03:04,651
and buried underground,

36
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:06,119
I'd rather

37
00:03:06,186 --> 00:03:07,453
do something more for others.

38
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:08,988
That way,

39
00:03:09,522 --> 00:03:10,990
I can keep teaching

40
00:03:12,158 --> 00:03:13,326
as a silent mentor in anatomy.

41
00:03:18,798 --> 00:03:20,266
Thank you, Professor Jiang.

42
00:03:29,242 --> 00:03:30,043
This past year,

43
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:31,444
I've never felt

44
00:03:31,511 --> 00:03:32,845
this calm before.

45
00:03:33,646 --> 00:03:34,247
I feel like

46
00:03:35,682 --> 00:03:37,083
I can accept any outcome.

47
00:03:39,185 --> 00:03:39,986
I'll let nature take its course.

48
00:03:47,126 --> 00:03:48,428
The night sky is beautiful tonight.

49
00:03:49,162 --> 00:03:50,029
Can you see it?

50
00:03:58,838 --> 00:03:59,272
Yes.

51
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:04,811
But in the city,

52
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:06,479
there's still too much light pollution.

53
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,648
I remember in Guizhou,

54
00:04:09,215 --> 00:04:10,149
all you had to do at night

55
00:04:10,850 --> 00:04:11,918
was look up to see the stars.

56
00:04:13,052 --> 00:04:13,987
Then

57
00:04:15,121 --> 00:04:17,156
find some time to visit again.

58
00:04:18,224 --> 00:04:19,092
We can go together

59
00:04:20,293 --> 00:04:20,960
and bring Senlin.

60
00:04:21,628 --> 00:04:22,762
There are green mountains and clear water there.

61
00:04:23,162 --> 00:04:23,997
The air is fresh.

62
00:04:25,164 --> 00:04:25,865
If we go in summer,

63
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:26,933
there are lots of fireflies too.

64
00:04:27,266 --> 00:04:28,334
He'd love it.

65
00:04:31,404 --> 00:04:32,005
Sure.

66
00:04:44,350 --> 00:04:46,486
Your speech at the conference that day

67
00:04:47,587 --> 00:04:48,655
carried a lot of weight.

68
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:51,958
I didn't expect that from you.

69
00:04:53,226 --> 00:04:55,728
You're usually so calm and restrained.

70
00:04:56,062 --> 00:04:57,630
It's rare to see you

71
00:04:58,031 --> 00:04:58,665
show such sharpness.

72
00:04:59,866 --> 00:05:00,733
You're too kind, President.

73
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:01,834
That day,

74
00:05:02,168 --> 00:05:02,969
I got a little emotional

75
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:04,637
and said what was on my mind.

76
00:05:06,572 --> 00:05:07,307
That's understandable.

77
00:05:08,041 --> 00:05:08,975
I completely understand.

78
00:05:09,809 --> 00:05:11,044
I asked you here today

79
00:05:11,511 --> 00:05:12,512
because there's something

80
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:14,247
I wanted to discuss with you first.

81
00:05:16,115 --> 00:05:19,352
The hospital plans to formally appoint you

82
00:05:19,552 --> 00:05:20,586
Director of Cardiology.

83
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:32,532
Thank you for the hospital leadership's trust.

84
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:35,768
What about Director Sheng?

85
00:05:36,636 --> 00:05:37,503
He'll remain where he is

86
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:38,871
and keep working hard.

87
00:05:40,873 --> 00:05:42,075
As for Director of the Heart Center,

88
00:05:42,642 --> 00:05:44,844
the hospital has decided to put that on hold

89
00:05:45,111 --> 00:05:46,346
pending further evaluation.

90
00:05:49,615 --> 00:05:50,116
Xiaofeng,

91
00:05:51,150 --> 00:05:52,085
you said in your speech

92
00:05:52,485 --> 00:05:54,454
that you didn't want to blindly chase performance

93
00:05:54,754 --> 00:05:55,755
at the expense of patients.

94
00:05:56,122 --> 00:05:56,923
That was very good.

95
00:05:58,024 --> 00:05:59,826
On putting patients first,

96
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,728
we are completely aligned.

97
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:03,563
There is no disagreement.

98
00:06:04,397 --> 00:06:05,465
But now that

99
00:06:05,798 --> 00:06:07,233
the acting title has been removed,

100
00:06:08,401 --> 00:06:09,602
your future work

101
00:06:09,802 --> 00:06:11,571
still needs to focus

102
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:12,805
on the department's development.

103
00:06:14,307 --> 00:06:15,975
Whether it's a department

104
00:06:16,175 --> 00:06:17,009
or an entire hospital,

105
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:19,645
we must shoulder social responsibility

106
00:06:20,012 --> 00:06:21,748
while also maintaining financial stability

107
00:06:22,348 --> 00:06:24,117
so we can serve patients better.

108
00:06:25,318 --> 00:06:26,152
Especially now,

109
00:06:26,586 --> 00:06:28,054
Cardiology's performance

110
00:06:28,855 --> 00:06:30,556
must improve further.

111
00:06:34,127 --> 00:06:34,560
Understood.

112
00:06:37,530 --> 00:06:38,398
President Chen has called me

113
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:39,198
several times.

114
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:40,400
First, he wants to know

115
00:06:40,466 --> 00:06:41,334
whether next month's schedule

116
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:41,934
has been finalized,

117
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:43,436
so he can arrange your visiting-surgeon dates.

118
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:44,771
Second,

119
00:06:45,004 --> 00:06:46,205
he's told me several times

120
00:06:46,506 --> 00:06:47,840
that he wants you to mentor their junior doctors.

121
00:06:48,474 --> 00:06:48,908
Director,

122
00:06:50,176 --> 00:06:51,077
whenever I go to Qinghai,

123
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:54,413
I get some altitude sickness.

124
00:06:55,214 --> 00:06:56,249
It's like that at first.

125
00:06:57,450 --> 00:06:58,284
After a few trips, you'll get used to it.

126
00:06:59,252 --> 00:06:59,752
Dr. Fang.

127
00:07:01,187 --> 00:07:01,721
What is it?

128
00:07:04,624 --> 00:07:05,491
I have a request.

129
00:07:14,534 --> 00:07:15,034
A transfer.

130
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:16,068
Yes.

131
00:07:16,736 --> 00:07:17,870
I want to transfer to Critical Care.

132
00:07:18,604 --> 00:07:19,038
Why?

133
00:07:20,306 --> 00:07:21,607
I've actually been thinking about it for a long time.

134
00:07:22,375 --> 00:07:23,009
I've always been

135
00:07:23,042 --> 00:07:23,810
very interested in

136
00:07:23,843 --> 00:07:24,644
critical care medicine.

137
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:26,446
It's also part of

138
00:07:26,479 --> 00:07:27,413
my next career plan.

139
00:07:29,649 --> 00:07:30,883
I was just telling Lin Yi

140
00:07:31,918 --> 00:07:33,386
that building up Cardiac Surgery

141
00:07:34,654 --> 00:07:36,422
depends on both of you.

142
00:07:37,156 --> 00:07:38,224
If you leave, then

143
00:07:38,391 --> 00:07:39,792
who will handle postoperative monitoring

144
00:07:39,892 --> 00:07:41,360
for all of Lin Yi's patients?

145
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:44,530
Together, you two achieve more than either one alone.

146
00:07:45,431 --> 00:07:46,199
Can't you

147
00:07:46,365 --> 00:07:47,366
consider the bigger picture?

148
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:48,434
The development of the general ICU system

149
00:07:48,434 --> 00:07:49,335
and coordination

150
00:07:50,069 --> 00:07:51,838
with all the surgeons

151
00:07:51,871 --> 00:07:53,272
was never my work alone.

152
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:54,907
Director Wang Xu

153
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:55,675
will be back next month.

154
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:56,642
And Du and the others

155
00:07:56,642 --> 00:07:57,610
can already handle the work.

156
00:07:58,077 --> 00:07:59,312
There are also two visiting doctors.

157
00:07:59,545 --> 00:08:00,213
The general ICU

158
00:08:00,213 --> 00:08:01,047
has enough staff.

159
00:08:01,681 --> 00:08:03,649
I promise to complete a proper handover.

160
00:08:06,385 --> 00:08:06,786
Lin Yi.

161
00:08:07,687 --> 00:08:08,454
Did you know about this?

162
00:08:12,592 --> 00:08:13,092
Dr. Fang.

163
00:08:14,393 --> 00:08:15,361
Then I'll be honest.

164
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,164
If you go to Critical Care,

165
00:08:18,531 --> 00:08:19,532
do you think you can achieve

166
00:08:19,532 --> 00:08:20,967
the same results you have now?

167
00:08:22,134 --> 00:08:22,768
Without

168
00:08:22,768 --> 00:08:24,270
an outstanding lead surgeon like Lin Yi

169
00:08:24,370 --> 00:08:25,571
charging ahead,

170
00:08:25,872 --> 00:08:27,306
how would the value of postoperative care

171
00:08:27,373 --> 00:08:28,174
even be demonstrated?

172
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:31,878
I don't approve.

173
00:08:32,278 --> 00:08:32,745
Director Sheng.

174
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:33,546
You should get back to work.

175
00:08:34,113 --> 00:08:34,814
We still have things to discuss.

176
00:08:47,493 --> 00:08:48,127
Why does she want to leave?

177
00:08:51,130 --> 00:08:51,731
She...

178
00:08:53,399 --> 00:08:53,933
She's wanted to go

179
00:08:53,966 --> 00:08:54,367
to the ICU

180
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:54,834
for a long time.

181
00:08:56,836 --> 00:08:57,603
I feel at ease

182
00:08:58,504 --> 00:08:59,906
entrusting your patients to her.

183
00:09:01,274 --> 00:09:02,208
I won't let her leave.

184
00:09:03,109 --> 00:09:04,143
You may have broken up,

185
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:05,711
but professionally,

186
00:09:05,878 --> 00:09:06,445
she should still

187
00:09:06,512 --> 00:09:07,813
work closely with you.

188
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:20,126
Xiaoran.

189
00:09:32,204 --> 00:09:33,272
When did you decide?

190
00:09:36,542 --> 00:09:37,443
I've been thinking about it for a while.

191
00:09:42,281 --> 00:09:43,749
After meeting Director Ji,

192
00:09:44,984 --> 00:09:46,485
the idea became even clearer.

193
00:09:53,559 --> 00:09:54,760
Does it have anything to do with me?

194
00:09:59,732 --> 00:10:00,600
No.

195
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:05,438
I didn't think so.

196
00:10:13,646 --> 00:10:14,847
You heard it just now.

197
00:10:15,548 --> 00:10:16,849
This is my career plan.

198
00:10:19,719 --> 00:10:20,519
But didn't you come to Dongli

199
00:10:21,554 --> 00:10:22,455
because you liked

200
00:10:22,488 --> 00:10:23,255
the general ICU model

201
00:10:23,255 --> 00:10:24,190
in the first place?

202
00:10:25,224 --> 00:10:26,392
I still like

203
00:10:26,425 --> 00:10:27,627
the general ICU model.

204
00:10:29,362 --> 00:10:30,096
I just feel

205
00:10:30,096 --> 00:10:31,530
I need a bigger challenge.

206
00:10:35,868 --> 00:10:37,136
Director Sheng doesn't agree.

207
00:10:39,405 --> 00:10:40,373
What are you going to do?

208
00:10:43,709 --> 00:10:45,411
If he says no once, I'll ask twice.

209
00:10:45,478 --> 00:10:47,079
If he says no twice, I'll ask three times.

210
00:10:47,847 --> 00:10:49,115
And if that still fails, I'll resign.

211
00:10:49,215 --> 00:10:49,915
You can't resign.

212
00:10:52,451 --> 00:10:52,985
There's no need.

213
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:01,427
I don't want things to get ugly either.

214
00:11:02,194 --> 00:11:03,195
But you saw it too.

215
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:06,432
He refuses my transfer

216
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:09,168
only because of you,

217
00:11:12,171 --> 00:11:13,472
because he wants me to cover for you.

218
00:11:18,811 --> 00:11:19,478
Director Lin,

219
00:11:20,246 --> 00:11:21,347
you're a surgical genius,

220
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:22,848
but I want to become

221
00:11:22,882 --> 00:11:24,183
a professional Dr. Fang,

222
00:11:25,151 --> 00:11:26,252
not someone defined by another person.

223
00:11:29,688 --> 00:11:30,690
A surgical genius.

224
00:11:32,324 --> 00:11:33,526
A foolish boyfriend.

225
00:11:50,142 --> 00:11:51,811
Critical care doctors

226
00:11:52,244 --> 00:11:53,813
are naturally highly independent.

227
00:11:54,914 --> 00:11:56,449
One person can be an entire unit.

228
00:11:57,783 --> 00:11:59,185
That's the path I want to take.

229
00:12:01,721 --> 00:12:03,255
If you really go to the ICU,

230
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:06,559
you won't work here anymore.

231
00:12:39,558 --> 00:12:40,126
Director Lin,

232
00:12:41,026 --> 00:12:42,128
you're a surgical genius,

233
00:12:43,195 --> 00:12:43,996
but I also want to become

234
00:12:44,096 --> 00:12:45,397
a professional Dr. Fang,

235
00:12:46,398 --> 00:12:47,366
not someone defined by another person.

236
00:13:31,010 --> 00:13:31,477
Director Zhou.

237
00:13:32,077 --> 00:13:32,711
This matter

238
00:13:33,312 --> 00:13:34,413
is indeed a little difficult.

239
00:13:34,914 --> 00:13:35,614
I understand.

240
00:13:36,081 --> 00:13:37,016
That's why I came to ask

241
00:13:37,116 --> 00:13:37,783
whether there's another way

242
00:13:37,783 --> 00:13:38,684
to make the transfer happen.

243
00:13:39,885 --> 00:13:41,253
For example, could Critical Care

244
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,721
request a temporary staff secondment?

245
00:13:46,292 --> 00:13:47,026
The main issue is that

246
00:13:47,092 --> 00:13:48,160
this involves an interdepartmental adjustment.

247
00:13:48,727 --> 00:13:50,262
If Director Sheng doesn't agree,

248
00:13:50,596 --> 00:13:51,430
Human Resources

249
00:13:51,530 --> 00:13:52,731
can't conveniently intervene directly.

250
00:13:53,632 --> 00:13:54,800
Otherwise, wouldn't that intensify

251
00:13:54,967 --> 00:13:56,135
the conflict between departments?

252
00:13:56,869 --> 00:13:59,004
We still recommend resolving it through friendly discussion.

253
00:14:13,552 --> 00:14:14,053
That's all

254
00:14:14,119 --> 00:14:15,087
for yesterday's patient updates.

255
00:14:16,755 --> 00:14:18,324
Before we adjourn,

256
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:19,091
I'd like to announce something.

257
00:14:21,627 --> 00:14:22,428
Dr. Fang previously

258
00:14:22,428 --> 00:14:24,129
submitted a request to transfer

259
00:14:24,163 --> 00:14:25,364
to Critical Care.

260
00:14:29,168 --> 00:14:29,768
I've approved it.

261
00:14:31,604 --> 00:14:33,405
So starting next Monday,

262
00:14:33,572 --> 00:14:34,206
Dr. Fang

263
00:14:34,506 --> 00:14:36,008
will report to Critical Care.

264
00:14:37,276 --> 00:14:38,110
Before the official transfer,

265
00:14:38,143 --> 00:14:39,411
there will be a two-month transition period.

266
00:14:39,678 --> 00:14:41,146
I hope the relevant colleagues

267
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:43,082
will assist Dr. Fang

268
00:14:43,249 --> 00:14:44,283
with a smooth handover.

269
00:14:45,184 --> 00:14:46,852
Let us wish Dr. Fang

270
00:14:47,152 --> 00:14:48,354
every success

271
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,121
in her new position.

272
00:14:50,923 --> 00:14:51,890
Thank you, Director Sheng.

273
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:04,803
Dr. Fang.

274
00:15:05,037 --> 00:15:05,704
Dr. Fang.

275
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,041
What is it?

276
00:15:10,109 --> 00:15:11,076
Are you really leaving?

277
00:15:12,044 --> 00:15:12,444
Yes.

278
00:15:13,479 --> 00:15:14,480
You shouldn't be surprised.

279
00:15:14,913 --> 00:15:16,682
I just hate to see you go.

280
00:15:18,517 --> 00:15:19,985
We're still in the same hospital.

281
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:21,253
We'll still see each other.

282
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:22,454
Dr. Fang,

283
00:15:22,955 --> 00:15:23,956
I used to think you were

284
00:15:23,956 --> 00:15:24,923
gentle and capable.

285
00:15:25,224 --> 00:15:27,426
Now I realize you're really cool too.

286
00:15:28,027 --> 00:15:28,994
This is enough to be cool?

287
00:15:29,528 --> 00:15:30,362
You can do it too.

288
00:15:30,796 --> 00:15:31,263
I'll try.

289
00:15:31,997 --> 00:15:32,464
Dr. Fang.

290
00:15:33,165 --> 00:15:34,233
Director Sheng refused

291
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:35,467
your transfer before, didn't he?

292
00:15:36,035 --> 00:15:37,436
Yes. He kept refusing.

293
00:15:38,203 --> 00:15:38,871
Then do you know

294
00:15:38,904 --> 00:15:39,838
why he suddenly agreed?

295
00:15:41,507 --> 00:15:42,241
You know?

296
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:43,042
We do.

297
00:15:43,709 --> 00:15:44,643
We both heard it.

298
00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:46,845
It was Director Lin.

299
00:15:47,646 --> 00:15:48,514
He argued with Director Sheng for ages

300
00:15:48,547 --> 00:15:49,882
over your transfer.

301
00:15:50,516 --> 00:15:51,250
He said if Director Sheng

302
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:51,784
still refused,

303
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:52,785
he'd quit too.

304
00:15:58,490 --> 00:15:59,425
I'm formally requesting

305
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:01,327
a transfer to the ICU.

306
00:16:05,431 --> 00:16:06,165
What are you trying to do?

307
00:16:09,435 --> 00:16:11,170
Director Ji in Critical Care

308
00:16:11,403 --> 00:16:12,237
is very short-staffed.

309
00:16:13,072 --> 00:16:13,872
Originally,

310
00:16:13,872 --> 00:16:14,773
she wanted Dr. Fang to go.

311
00:16:15,107 --> 00:16:16,408
But since you wouldn't let her,

312
00:16:17,409 --> 00:16:18,277
she contacted me instead

313
00:16:18,344 --> 00:16:20,212
and asked whether I could go.

314
00:16:20,879 --> 00:16:21,613
I said I could.

315
00:16:23,215 --> 00:16:24,650
You're here because of Fang Xiaoran, aren't you?

316
00:16:25,751 --> 00:16:27,653
Aren't you two no longer together?

317
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:28,287
We're not together.

318
00:16:28,754 --> 00:16:29,388
We're just

319
00:16:29,455 --> 00:16:30,089
ordinary colleagues now,

320
00:16:30,689 --> 00:16:31,957
and both members of the Dongli family.

321
00:16:32,191 --> 00:16:32,891
Speak properly.

322
00:16:37,629 --> 00:16:38,597
I think the reason

323
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:39,398
you gave for rejecting her last time

324
00:16:39,398 --> 00:16:40,232
was very unfair.

325
00:16:43,502 --> 00:16:44,269
Dr. Fang is

326
00:16:44,269 --> 00:16:45,004
an excellent doctor.

327
00:16:46,672 --> 00:16:47,673
She has always been professional

328
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:48,474
in the general ICU.

329
00:16:49,408 --> 00:16:50,109
A good doctor should

330
00:16:50,109 --> 00:16:51,009
have ambitions of their own.

331
00:16:53,645 --> 00:16:54,279
Now that she's found

332
00:16:54,313 --> 00:16:55,347
her professional calling,

333
00:16:59,084 --> 00:17:00,319
I hope you'll let her pursue it.

334
00:17:07,559 --> 00:17:08,727
If you still refuse,

335
00:17:11,563 --> 00:17:12,564
you can approve my transfer instead.

336
00:17:23,409 --> 00:17:24,243
All right. I understand.

337
00:17:40,125 --> 00:17:41,226
But are you sure

338
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:42,561
Director Lin wants Dr. Fang

339
00:17:42,594 --> 00:17:43,429
to know all this?

340
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:46,432
I don't care anymore.

341
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:48,467
I may be single,

342
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,368
but the couple I ship

343
00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:50,235
has to get married.

344
00:18:05,517 --> 00:18:06,452
What should we eat later?

345
00:18:07,653 --> 00:18:08,554
Anything. You choose.

346
00:18:09,555 --> 00:18:11,156
Let's order delivery. I'll do it.

347
00:18:11,790 --> 00:18:12,224
Okay.

348
00:18:15,527 --> 00:18:16,728
Why are you eating fruit now?

349
00:18:16,962 --> 00:18:18,030
We're about to have dinner.

350
00:18:19,031 --> 00:18:20,065
Offerings shouldn't go to waste.

351
00:18:24,670 --> 00:18:25,237
Who is it?

352
00:18:32,644 --> 00:18:33,245
I couldn't find anyone

353
00:18:33,245 --> 00:18:33,912
to eat with on Qingming Festival,

354
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:34,613
so I had to come to you.

355
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:39,318
What? Am I not welcome?

356
00:18:40,919 --> 00:18:41,920
Or are you hiding someone at home?

357
00:18:49,428 --> 00:18:51,463
You two eat.

358
00:18:53,732 --> 00:18:55,200
I'll eat by myself.

359
00:18:55,367 --> 00:18:56,235
Let's eat together.

360
00:19:03,542 --> 00:19:04,476
I went to sweep the graves today

361
00:19:05,944 --> 00:19:06,712
and brought some qingtuan.

362
00:19:14,052 --> 00:19:15,387
You went to see Xiaorui today too?

363
00:19:18,557 --> 00:19:19,625
I was wondering

364
00:19:20,792 --> 00:19:22,394
who left those two bouquets.

365
00:19:25,731 --> 00:19:26,598
I'll order some food.

366
00:19:27,466 --> 00:19:27,866
Okay.

367
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:28,934
I...

368
00:19:30,869 --> 00:19:32,037
I'll change my shoes first.

369
00:19:38,610 --> 00:19:38,911
Um...

370
00:19:39,311 --> 00:19:40,546
These qingtuan are pretty good.

371
00:19:47,085 --> 00:19:48,921
We bought them from the same shop.

372
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:51,023
Yes. The same one.

373
00:19:52,224 --> 00:19:52,624
But

374
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:54,993
the packaging changed this year.

375
00:19:58,030 --> 00:19:58,830
The flavor hasn't.

376
00:20:07,439 --> 00:20:07,773
Here.

377
00:20:12,110 --> 00:20:13,278
I haven't had any water all day.

378
00:20:22,921 --> 00:20:23,755
Sit down.

379
00:20:32,965 --> 00:20:34,433
He didn't tell me

380
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,001
you two were going to the cemetery.

381
00:20:36,935 --> 00:20:37,469
Otherwise,

382
00:20:38,103 --> 00:20:40,572
we could've gone together.

383
00:20:48,947 --> 00:20:49,615
Thank you.

384
00:20:52,284 --> 00:20:52,951
For what?

385
00:20:56,488 --> 00:20:57,122
I heard you're also

386
00:20:57,155 --> 00:20:58,290
transferring to Critical Care.

387
00:21:02,427 --> 00:21:04,963
I considered it.

388
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:06,765
I wanted to challenge myself.

389
00:21:09,234 --> 00:21:10,636
What could you do there?

390
00:21:14,373 --> 00:21:15,507
Let me look it up.

391
00:21:17,476 --> 00:21:19,044
What can

392
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:20,345
a cardiac surgeon do in Critical Care?

393
00:21:23,248 --> 00:21:24,249
Work as artificial intelligence?

394
00:21:30,555 --> 00:21:31,356
Artificial intelligence

395
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:34,826
can be useful,

396
00:21:39,031 --> 00:21:40,332
but you have to verify it carefully.

397
00:21:44,503 --> 00:21:45,237
Exactly.

398
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:47,439
It still has plenty of flaws.

399
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:49,608
But give it some time

400
00:21:50,042 --> 00:21:51,176
and let it keep updating.

401
00:21:52,411 --> 00:21:53,545
It can always improve.

402
00:22:21,573 --> 00:22:22,207
Don't you two

403
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:25,110
have anything

404
00:22:25,143 --> 00:22:26,345
to tell me?

405
00:22:33,719 --> 00:22:34,286
Well...

406
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:36,154
Happy holiday.

407
00:22:38,423 --> 00:22:39,491
I've been too busy lately

408
00:22:39,691 --> 00:22:41,026
to formally

409
00:22:41,093 --> 00:22:42,227
congratulate my brother on his promotion.

410
00:22:43,228 --> 00:22:45,163
May your future be bright and your ambitions fulfilled.

411
00:22:45,464 --> 00:22:46,164
Stay alert in times of peace.

412
00:22:51,503 --> 00:22:53,071
This appointment shows

413
00:22:53,071 --> 00:22:53,872
the hospital leadership still agrees

414
00:22:53,872 --> 00:22:55,207
with what you said last time.

415
00:22:56,608 --> 00:22:57,209
Not necessarily.

416
00:22:58,343 --> 00:22:59,945
One carrot came with two sticks.

417
00:23:00,278 --> 00:23:01,747
The rules haven't changed at all.

418
00:23:02,848 --> 00:23:03,682
What do you mean?

419
00:23:07,919 --> 00:23:08,787
President Wang said

420
00:23:09,788 --> 00:23:10,689
that after my promotion,

421
00:23:11,256 --> 00:23:13,158
I still have to carry the banner of performance,

422
00:23:13,759 --> 00:23:15,494
even higher than before.

423
00:23:19,865 --> 00:23:21,199
And what's the other stick?

424
00:23:26,471 --> 00:23:27,906
That research project you submitted before—

425
00:23:28,473 --> 00:23:31,209
I'm not particularly opposed to it.

426
00:23:32,077 --> 00:23:33,044
But I heard

427
00:23:33,078 --> 00:23:35,947
there may be some connection

428
00:23:36,314 --> 00:23:37,149
with a female sales representative from Mianpei.

429
00:23:37,716 --> 00:23:38,517
What's going on?

430
00:23:39,084 --> 00:23:39,951
Professor Jiang Wei

431
00:23:40,051 --> 00:23:41,253
helped introduce us

432
00:23:41,319 --> 00:23:42,320
for this project.

433
00:23:43,188 --> 00:23:44,923
Manager Ouyang was her student.

434
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:46,558
Before entering sales,

435
00:23:46,591 --> 00:23:47,926
she was also a clinician.

436
00:23:48,427 --> 00:23:49,294
This project

437
00:23:49,494 --> 00:23:50,395
has nothing to do with her sales role.

438
00:23:50,429 --> 00:23:51,329
There is no connection whatsoever,

439
00:23:51,663 --> 00:23:52,964
and certainly no financial interest involved.

440
00:23:55,867 --> 00:23:57,502
Of course I believe you.

441
00:23:58,303 --> 00:23:59,371
But you need to understand:

442
00:23:59,771 --> 00:24:01,673
facts are one thing,

443
00:24:02,874 --> 00:24:03,375
but public opinion

444
00:24:04,176 --> 00:24:05,443
is another.

445
00:24:06,111 --> 00:24:07,612
Those topics online

446
00:24:07,712 --> 00:24:09,147
are still being discussed.

447
00:24:09,614 --> 00:24:11,116
Manager Ouyang and I

448
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:12,350
have nothing to hide.

449
00:24:12,551 --> 00:24:13,752
We can withstand any investigation from above.

450
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,721
Let me be more direct.

451
00:24:17,756 --> 00:24:18,423
The hospital

452
00:24:19,224 --> 00:24:20,959
plans to develop you

453
00:24:21,026 --> 00:24:22,394
as a key talent.

454
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:24,362
Your future career path

455
00:24:24,696 --> 00:24:25,797
has already been mapped out.

456
00:24:26,364 --> 00:24:28,333
Why ruin your prospects

457
00:24:28,867 --> 00:24:30,368
over a romantic relationship?

458
00:24:31,036 --> 00:24:31,703
Actually, this problem

459
00:24:31,770 --> 00:24:32,604
is easy to solve.

460
00:24:33,004 --> 00:24:34,105
As long as the two of you

461
00:24:34,439 --> 00:24:35,707
have no business dealings,

462
00:24:36,007 --> 00:24:37,042
how you interact privately

463
00:24:37,709 --> 00:24:38,810
is your own affair.

464
00:24:41,346 --> 00:24:43,748
President Wang can make demands like that?

465
00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:46,351
That specific?

466
00:24:48,286 --> 00:24:49,254
Why aren't you surprised at all?

467
00:24:51,823 --> 00:24:53,091
You knew about the two of them too?

468
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:56,294
He knew?

469
00:24:57,963 --> 00:24:59,231
I only told you two.

470
00:25:05,570 --> 00:25:05,904
Then...

471
00:25:06,705 --> 00:25:07,973
does Ouyang know yet?

472
00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:11,276
I haven't told her.

473
00:25:14,613 --> 00:25:16,014
President Wang wants me to replace her.

474
00:25:17,516 --> 00:25:18,149
But if she's replaced,

475
00:25:18,149 --> 00:25:18,917
where can she go?

476
00:25:20,185 --> 00:25:21,553
At a company like Mianpei,

477
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:22,654
the good territories

478
00:25:22,754 --> 00:25:24,089
have already been divided up

479
00:25:24,089 --> 00:25:24,890
among experienced senior salespeople.

480
00:25:27,526 --> 00:25:28,193
Then...

481
00:25:28,593 --> 00:25:29,361
maybe...

482
00:25:29,961 --> 00:25:30,729
maybe just let it go.

483
00:25:31,429 --> 00:25:32,631
At least she won't lose her job.

484
00:25:33,765 --> 00:25:34,332
Besides,

485
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:35,534
a proud person shouldn't

486
00:25:37,569 --> 00:25:38,203
accept...

487
00:25:39,604 --> 00:25:40,705
accept charity.

488
00:25:41,172 --> 00:25:41,706
Right?

489
00:25:49,247 --> 00:25:50,215
No matter what,

490
00:25:51,516 --> 00:25:52,517
it's time the two of us

491
00:25:54,152 --> 00:25:55,487
reached a decision.

492
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:23,214
So that's what President Wang said.

493
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:25,884
What about your side?

494
00:26:26,518 --> 00:26:27,519
Is the company pressuring you?

495
00:26:28,486 --> 00:26:29,254
On my end,

496
00:26:29,921 --> 00:26:31,556
they don't interfere that much.

497
00:26:33,091 --> 00:26:34,125
That makes sense.

498
00:26:34,426 --> 00:26:36,528
You just became a full director.

499
00:26:36,828 --> 00:26:37,429
You need to be more careful

500
00:26:37,495 --> 00:26:38,596
about everything.

501
00:26:39,965 --> 00:26:40,932
But don't worry.

502
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:42,801
You focus on being a good director.

503
00:26:43,268 --> 00:26:44,869
I'm the top salesperson now.

504
00:26:45,170 --> 00:26:46,504
My boss won't want to give up

505
00:26:46,638 --> 00:26:47,572
their top performer.

506
00:26:49,507 --> 00:26:50,742
That's not what I meant.

507
00:26:51,910 --> 00:26:52,744
What they're worried about

508
00:26:52,744 --> 00:26:53,445
is simply this:

509
00:26:53,545 --> 00:26:54,446
the Director of Cardiology

510
00:26:54,679 --> 00:26:56,047
and a sales manager from Mianpei

511
00:26:56,414 --> 00:26:57,482
having an unclear relationship.

512
00:26:57,882 --> 00:26:59,117
Then if that's the problem,

513
00:27:00,919 --> 00:27:01,686
I'll just stop being

514
00:27:02,187 --> 00:27:03,254
department director.

515
00:27:07,425 --> 00:27:08,093
Stop being director?

516
00:27:10,362 --> 00:27:11,196
Are you crazy?

517
00:27:11,830 --> 00:27:12,731
I'm serious.

518
00:27:13,999 --> 00:27:15,367
I'll step down from the administrative role.

519
00:27:15,934 --> 00:27:16,835
Without authority to approve

520
00:27:16,868 --> 00:27:17,836
devices or consumables,

521
00:27:18,837 --> 00:27:20,238
there can be no suspicion, right?

522
00:27:20,639 --> 00:27:21,306
Even without being department director,

523
00:27:21,373 --> 00:27:22,507
I can still be a doctor.

524
00:27:23,208 --> 00:27:24,609
I can see patients and perform procedures,

525
00:27:24,909 --> 00:27:26,478
and put all my energy into clinical work

526
00:27:26,845 --> 00:27:27,746
and our cardiomyopathy

527
00:27:27,746 --> 00:27:28,313
research project.

528
00:27:29,447 --> 00:27:30,248
Wouldn't that be fine?

529
00:27:38,623 --> 00:27:39,190
Why?

530
00:27:44,262 --> 00:27:45,030
Do you remember

531
00:27:45,030 --> 00:27:45,864
what this place is?

532
00:27:57,609 --> 00:27:58,043
I remember.

533
00:27:59,044 --> 00:28:00,245
It's where you broke up with me.

534
00:28:00,545 --> 00:28:01,312
You broke up with me.

535
00:28:02,113 --> 00:28:02,614
I...

536
00:28:03,548 --> 00:28:04,582
It doesn't matter.

537
00:28:08,586 --> 00:28:09,654
When I was in school,

538
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:12,190
I was closed off

539
00:28:13,324 --> 00:28:13,892
and conflicted.

540
00:28:15,794 --> 00:28:16,594
It wasn't until I met you

541
00:28:18,163 --> 00:28:19,764
that I slowly began to open up.

542
00:28:22,434 --> 00:28:23,802
You were always by my side,

543
00:28:26,104 --> 00:28:26,671
staying with me,

544
00:28:28,506 --> 00:28:29,307
supporting me,

545
00:28:30,575 --> 00:28:32,243
encouraging and accepting me.

546
00:28:37,582 --> 00:28:39,117
In the first twenty years of my life,

547
00:28:41,453 --> 00:28:43,088
you were the brightest light I encountered.

548
00:28:46,991 --> 00:28:47,625
Now,

549
00:28:48,393 --> 00:28:49,527
more than ten years have passed,

550
00:28:51,429 --> 00:28:52,430
and you haven't changed at all.

551
00:28:53,531 --> 00:28:54,432
To me,

552
00:28:56,935 --> 00:28:58,236
you're still just as radiant.

553
00:29:00,505 --> 00:29:01,473
The only difference

554
00:29:02,373 --> 00:29:03,241
is that this time,

555
00:29:05,877 --> 00:29:07,078
I don't want to lose you again.

556
00:29:11,082 --> 00:29:12,083
I'm not acting on impulse.

557
00:29:13,551 --> 00:29:14,652
I've asked myself seriously.

558
00:29:16,454 --> 00:29:17,822
If I must make a choice,

559
00:29:19,557 --> 00:29:21,392
you're the one I want to hold on to.

560
00:29:24,562 --> 00:29:24,929
Ouyang,

561
00:29:26,331 --> 00:29:27,332
this is how I truly feel.

562
00:29:33,071 --> 00:29:34,038
Will you take

563
00:29:34,038 --> 00:29:34,773
this leap with me?

564
00:29:50,255 --> 00:29:50,822
I know

565
00:29:52,090 --> 00:29:52,724
For you,

566
00:29:52,724 --> 00:29:53,892
this is a major decision.

567
00:29:54,592 --> 00:29:55,827
You don't have to answer now.

568
00:29:56,494 --> 00:29:57,228
Take your time to think.

569
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:07,972
I will.

570
00:30:29,761 --> 00:30:30,428
Let's take the leap.

571
00:30:31,062 --> 00:30:31,796
Together.

572
00:30:51,850 --> 00:30:52,550
Director, how was Qinghai?

573
00:31:36,227 --> 00:31:37,795
Every time I go,

574
00:31:38,997 --> 00:31:39,797
I get off the plane and go straight onstage,

575
00:31:39,864 --> 00:31:41,032
then leave the stage and get back on the plane.

576
00:31:41,065 --> 00:31:42,200
I never get to see anything.

577
00:31:42,367 --> 00:31:43,201
When's today's surgery?

578
00:31:45,069 --> 00:31:46,037
There's one this afternoon.

579
00:31:46,371 --> 00:31:47,071
But first, we need to see

580
00:31:47,305 --> 00:31:48,239
the patient in Bed 8.

581
00:31:48,239 --> 00:31:48,873
Why?

582
00:31:50,975 --> 00:31:51,342
Did you forget?

583
00:31:52,911 --> 00:31:53,544
Before closing the chest, you specifically told me

584
00:31:53,945 --> 00:31:55,613
that as soon as you returned from Qinghai,

585
00:31:55,813 --> 00:31:56,414
you'd check on him first.

586
00:31:56,447 --> 00:31:57,415
Bed 8?

587
00:31:58,750 --> 00:31:59,317
Mitral valve prolapse?

588
00:32:00,551 --> 00:32:01,586
No.

589
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:03,054
Aortic dissection.

590
00:32:03,855 --> 00:32:04,656
Bed 7 is mitral valve prolapse.

591
00:32:09,193 --> 00:32:10,528
Bed 7 had bypass surgery.

592
00:32:11,429 --> 00:32:12,830
I remember we recently had

593
00:32:14,732 --> 00:32:16,000
a patient with mitral valve prolapse.

594
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:17,335
That was Xiao Chen.

595
00:32:19,304 --> 00:32:20,872
He was discharged a long time ago.

596
00:32:21,205 --> 00:32:21,906
Director, are you suffering

597
00:32:32,083 --> 00:32:32,984
from altitude sickness?

598
00:32:33,051 --> 00:32:33,785
In the future,

599
00:32:52,103 --> 00:32:53,471
you'll meet countless patients

600
00:32:53,805 --> 00:32:54,972
in the hospital.

601
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:56,808
They may seem like

602
00:32:56,874 --> 00:32:58,676
strangers with nothing to do with you.

603
00:33:00,278 --> 00:33:00,878
I hope

604
00:33:00,912 --> 00:33:02,280
you remember every one of them.

605
00:33:02,914 --> 00:33:04,048
Remember their names,

606
00:33:06,150 --> 00:33:06,751
their faces,

607
00:33:07,719 --> 00:33:08,453
and their smiles.

608
00:33:11,356 --> 00:33:11,789
Director.

609
00:33:17,595 --> 00:33:18,129
I'm fine.

610
00:33:37,515 --> 00:33:38,750
I failed to fulfill

611
00:33:38,783 --> 00:33:39,751
my duty as a doctor.

612
00:33:40,651 --> 00:33:41,519
Somewhere along this path,

613
00:33:42,587 --> 00:33:43,488
I had already forgotten

614
00:33:44,322 --> 00:33:45,123
why I started.

615
00:33:45,189 --> 00:33:46,357
But fortunately,

616
00:33:47,725 --> 00:33:48,426
I still remember

617
00:33:49,193 --> 00:33:49,927
the faces

618
00:33:50,928 --> 00:33:51,829
that accompanied me along the way.

619
00:33:53,531 --> 00:33:55,366
Those patients—

620
00:33:56,667 --> 00:33:57,402
my patients.

621
00:33:59,103 --> 00:34:00,071
Can I stop going

622
00:34:02,874 --> 00:34:04,275
to the expert clinic in Qinghai?

623
00:34:05,410 --> 00:34:06,277
Stop going?

624
00:34:10,648 --> 00:34:11,182
Is it the altitude sickness?

625
00:34:13,084 --> 00:34:14,118
Are you too tired?

626
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:15,186
No.

627
00:34:16,387 --> 00:34:16,854
I simply don't want to go anymore.

628
00:34:19,023 --> 00:34:20,124
All right.

629
00:34:23,227 --> 00:34:23,594
I'll speak with

630
00:34:23,694 --> 00:34:24,095
President Chen in Qinghai.

631
00:34:24,128 --> 00:34:25,196
We'll pause it for now.

632
00:34:25,563 --> 00:34:26,197
Take some time to rest.

633
00:34:26,230 --> 00:34:26,964
And Huiyang too.

634
00:34:27,665 --> 00:34:28,332
I hope you can

635
00:34:30,201 --> 00:34:30,935
find someone to replace me.

636
00:34:30,935 --> 00:34:31,769
I want to stop all my visiting surgeries.

637
00:34:33,070 --> 00:34:33,871
I want to stop

638
00:34:33,905 --> 00:34:34,572
all my visiting surgeries.

639
00:34:37,241 --> 00:34:37,575
Of course,

640
00:34:38,042 --> 00:34:39,243
I'll finish the cases I've already accepted.

641
00:34:39,677 --> 00:34:40,812
Did something happen?

642
00:34:42,346 --> 00:34:43,414
operating meant saving lives.

643
00:34:44,482 --> 00:34:45,450
Every life saved was a victory,

644
00:34:46,150 --> 00:34:47,285
and the more, the better.

645
00:34:47,585 --> 00:34:48,386
But I was wrong.

646
00:34:49,086 --> 00:34:49,687
Doctors face

647
00:34:50,154 --> 00:34:50,888
more than diseases and organs.

648
00:34:50,888 --> 00:34:52,423
We face living, breathing people.

649
00:34:53,090 --> 00:34:54,325
Lately,

650
00:34:57,361 --> 00:34:58,196
I've been traveling and flying everywhere.

651
00:35:00,598 --> 00:35:01,833
But every time, I rush into the OR

652
00:35:04,235 --> 00:35:05,436
and rush back out.

653
00:35:05,503 --> 00:35:06,237
It looks like I've saved many people,

654
00:35:07,705 --> 00:35:09,040
but I never

655
00:35:09,974 --> 00:35:10,575
truly paid attention to them.

656
00:35:10,575 --> 00:35:11,709
I didn't even sign

657
00:35:12,477 --> 00:35:13,644
their discharge papers myself.

658
00:35:13,644 --> 00:35:14,278
I don't know my patients.

659
00:35:17,682 --> 00:35:18,716
I don't like that feeling.

660
00:35:22,386 --> 00:35:23,588
So what do you want to do?

661
00:35:25,890 --> 00:35:26,824
From now on,

662
00:35:29,193 --> 00:35:29,961
I want to devote

663
00:35:29,961 --> 00:35:30,561
all my energy

664
00:35:30,595 --> 00:35:31,662
to this hospital.

665
00:35:34,398 --> 00:35:35,066
I want to treat

666
00:35:35,066 --> 00:35:36,000
every patient seriously,

667
00:35:37,768 --> 00:35:38,569
operate on them,

668
00:35:39,470 --> 00:35:40,404
stay with them through recovery,

669
00:35:41,105 --> 00:35:42,039
and see them discharged.

670
00:35:44,809 --> 00:35:46,344
Patients entrust me with their lives.

671
00:35:47,612 --> 00:35:48,913
I don't want to betray that trust

672
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:53,951
by becoming nothing more than a surgical machine.

673
00:36:07,131 --> 00:36:07,865
So you think

674
00:36:07,965 --> 00:36:09,000
I turned you into

675
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:09,934
a surgical machine?

676
00:36:11,335 --> 00:36:12,203
You've treated me very well.

677
00:36:13,170 --> 00:36:13,905
Ever since you came,

678
00:36:14,839 --> 00:36:15,773
you've always looked out for me.

679
00:36:16,807 --> 00:36:17,408
This isn't about you,

680
00:36:18,442 --> 00:36:19,644
or about visiting surgeries.

681
00:36:20,211 --> 00:36:21,279
It's my own problem.

682
00:36:25,683 --> 00:36:26,484
I'm sorry I disappointed you.

683
00:36:29,253 --> 00:36:29,754
Lin Yi.

684
00:36:33,724 --> 00:36:34,792
I told you before

685
00:36:35,893 --> 00:36:36,794
that I would do everything I could

686
00:36:37,728 --> 00:36:39,797
to raise the department's academic standing

687
00:36:41,265 --> 00:36:42,433
and strengthen its influence.

688
00:36:44,535 --> 00:36:45,036
I meant it.

689
00:36:47,872 --> 00:36:49,073
I thought we were on the same path.

690
00:36:59,850 --> 00:37:01,185
I come from a family

691
00:37:01,252 --> 00:37:02,520
with an inherited cardiomyopathy gene.

692
00:37:04,121 --> 00:37:05,089
I can't see that far ahead.

693
00:37:07,992 --> 00:37:08,793
I only want to be

694
00:37:08,826 --> 00:37:09,627
an ordinary, good doctor.

695
00:37:40,992 --> 00:37:42,326
You need to remember all of this carefully.

696
00:37:44,328 --> 00:37:45,029
Dr. Fang

697
00:37:46,530 --> 00:37:47,398
has been waiting for you.

698
00:37:47,965 --> 00:37:48,633
Director Ji

699
00:37:48,633 --> 00:37:49,567
is in Shanghai for two days of training.

700
00:37:49,734 --> 00:37:50,401
She specifically asked me

701
00:37:50,468 --> 00:37:51,435
to take good care of you.

702
00:37:53,404 --> 00:37:54,872
I'm the head nurse in Critical Care.

703
00:37:55,239 --> 00:37:56,240
Everyone calls me Sister Mo.

704
00:37:57,008 --> 00:37:57,675
Hello, Sister Mo.

705
00:37:58,909 --> 00:38:00,411
Everyone, come over for a moment.

706
00:38:01,078 --> 00:38:01,612
Let me

707
00:38:01,646 --> 00:38:02,680
introduce everyone.

708
00:38:03,147 --> 00:38:04,448
This is Fang Xiaoran,

709
00:38:04,615 --> 00:38:05,182
Dr. Fang.

710
00:38:05,483 --> 00:38:06,984
Starting today, she has officially transferred

711
00:38:07,084 --> 00:38:08,185
to our ICU.

712
00:38:08,452 --> 00:38:09,720
From now on, we'll be comrades

713
00:38:09,787 --> 00:38:10,988
fighting side by side.

714
00:38:11,322 --> 00:38:13,157
Please take good care of me.

715
00:38:13,758 --> 00:38:14,392
Welcome, Dr. Fang.

716
00:38:14,492 --> 00:38:15,192
Welcome, Dr. Fang.

717
00:38:16,394 --> 00:38:17,094
Thank you, everyone.

718
00:38:17,528 --> 00:38:18,295
You're recovering very well.

719
00:38:18,429 --> 00:38:19,130
Everything looks normal.

720
00:38:20,164 --> 00:38:21,032
Thank you, Director Zhou.

721
00:38:21,632 --> 00:38:22,433
For your next follow-up,

722
00:38:22,466 --> 00:38:23,234
if you have trouble getting an appointment,

723
00:38:23,267 --> 00:38:24,035
come directly to me.

724
00:38:24,568 --> 00:38:25,269
Okay. Thank you.

725
00:38:27,104 --> 00:38:28,439
What's wrong? What happened?

726
00:38:38,149 --> 00:38:39,150
The babies are both doing well.

727
00:38:39,517 --> 00:38:40,318
They're both fine.

728
00:38:40,851 --> 00:38:42,386
It's really all thanks to Director Zhou.

729
00:38:43,054 --> 00:38:43,721
Isn't that right?

730
00:38:43,954 --> 00:38:45,756
My sister and I always say

731
00:38:45,990 --> 00:38:47,191
that both mother and child

732
00:38:47,358 --> 00:38:48,559
owe their lives to you

733
00:38:48,726 --> 00:38:49,960
and Professor Fang.

734
00:38:50,428 --> 00:38:51,595
What wonderful fate brought you together.

735
00:38:51,595 --> 00:38:52,196
Yes.

736
00:38:52,329 --> 00:38:52,997
We only did our duty.

737
00:38:54,165 --> 00:38:55,032
This is Hongxia.

738
00:38:55,533 --> 00:38:56,967
She's a relative of the Mu family.

739
00:38:57,201 --> 00:38:58,002
She and her husband

740
00:38:58,002 --> 00:38:59,070
also work in Dongjiang.

741
00:38:59,370 --> 00:39:00,271
They often help out

742
00:39:00,371 --> 00:39:01,238
at our patient support center.

743
00:39:01,639 --> 00:39:02,073
It's what we should do.

744
00:39:02,173 --> 00:39:02,673
Hello.

745
00:39:03,174 --> 00:39:03,708
Hello.

746
00:39:04,241 --> 00:39:04,909
How many months are you?

747
00:39:06,944 --> 00:39:07,878
A little over five months.

748
00:39:09,013 --> 00:39:10,247
It's stable now.

749
00:39:10,648 --> 00:39:12,016
I haven't had much discomfort.

750
00:39:12,316 --> 00:39:13,284
I eat and sleep well.

751
00:39:14,719 --> 00:39:15,453
You're young, after all.

752
00:39:17,555 --> 00:39:18,389
By the way, Director Zhou,

753
00:39:18,522 --> 00:39:19,690
our patient support center

754
00:39:19,690 --> 00:39:21,125
has an event this weekend.

755
00:39:21,492 --> 00:39:22,827
If you're free,

756
00:39:22,827 --> 00:39:23,828
come join us.

757
00:39:25,129 --> 00:39:26,163
I probably can't this weekend.

758
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:26,931
I still have meetings.

759
00:39:28,265 --> 00:39:28,766
All right.

760
00:39:30,634 --> 00:39:31,335
Everyone

761
00:39:31,335 --> 00:39:32,336
has been thinking about you.

762
00:39:33,070 --> 00:39:33,838
I'll definitely come when I have the chance.

763
00:39:34,071 --> 00:39:34,438
Good.

764
00:39:37,608 --> 00:39:38,042
Here, take one.

765
00:39:38,042 --> 00:39:38,542
What are you doing?

766
00:39:38,542 --> 00:39:39,510
It's a light bulb.

767
00:39:39,710 --> 00:39:40,044
Look.

768
00:39:40,911 --> 00:39:41,345
Go on.

769
00:39:41,846 --> 00:39:42,747
Go play.

770
00:39:45,082 --> 00:39:45,883
Slow down.

771
00:39:46,517 --> 00:39:47,752
Auntie has a baby in her belly.

772
00:39:47,752 --> 00:39:48,586
You have to protect her.

773
00:39:48,853 --> 00:39:49,286
It's okay.

774
00:39:49,286 --> 00:39:49,754
Got it.

775
00:39:51,088 --> 00:39:51,889
You don't need to work.

776
00:39:51,956 --> 00:39:52,957
We'll handle it.

777
00:39:53,357 --> 00:39:54,225
It's fine.

778
00:39:54,692 --> 00:39:55,526
This little bit of work

779
00:39:55,793 --> 00:39:56,394
won't tire me out.

780
00:39:57,361 --> 00:39:58,162
Let me help.

781
00:39:58,195 --> 00:39:59,063
You should rest.

782
00:39:59,063 --> 00:39:59,463
I'm fine.

783
00:40:02,066 --> 00:40:03,033
Auntie Hongxia.

784
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:05,269
There's water on the floor. Don't slip.

785
00:40:05,436 --> 00:40:06,237
Okay.

786
00:40:08,172 --> 00:40:09,073
I just mopped.

787
00:40:09,106 --> 00:40:09,874
Why is there water?

788
00:40:11,909 --> 00:40:12,376
Wait.

789
00:40:15,713 --> 00:40:16,447
Her water broke.

790
00:40:17,248 --> 00:40:17,748
Come, come.

791
00:40:17,948 --> 00:40:18,349
Sit down.

792
00:40:18,349 --> 00:40:19,016
Quick, there's a chair here.

793
00:40:19,016 --> 00:40:19,450
No.

794
00:40:19,917 --> 00:40:20,551
Call 120.

795
00:40:21,552 --> 00:40:22,052
Lie her down here.

796
00:40:22,787 --> 00:40:23,187
It's okay.

797
00:40:23,187 --> 00:40:23,487
Slowly.

798
00:40:23,521 --> 00:40:24,188
Don't panic.

799
00:40:24,488 --> 00:40:25,089
Come on, slowly.

800
00:40:25,990 --> 00:40:26,924
Don't rush. Don't rush.

801
00:40:28,526 --> 00:40:29,326
Her water broke.

802
00:40:30,427 --> 00:40:31,796
We have a pregnant woman about to deliver.

803
00:40:31,796 --> 00:40:32,429
Don't be nervous.

804
00:40:32,429 --> 00:40:33,130
It's okay. It's okay.

805
00:40:33,197 --> 00:40:33,764
Don't panic.

806
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:43,207
Premature rupture of membranes.

807
00:40:43,207 --> 00:40:44,108
The cervix is already one centimeter dilated.

808
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:45,209
She's having regular contractions.

809
00:40:45,276 --> 00:40:46,210
We need to get her to the hospital now.

810
00:40:52,750 --> 00:40:53,250
Director Pan.

811
00:40:53,717 --> 00:40:54,718
Thirty-year-old primigravida,

812
00:40:54,852 --> 00:40:55,586
at 25 weeks.

813
00:40:56,454 --> 00:40:57,054
Regular contractions.

814
00:40:57,254 --> 00:40:58,155
The cervix is already three centimeters dilated.

815
00:40:59,156 --> 00:40:59,924
Send her to the delivery room first.

816
00:41:00,524 --> 00:41:02,159
The Maternal and Infant Safety Office has opened a green channel.

817
00:41:02,626 --> 00:41:03,727
Neonatology and the blood bank

818
00:41:03,761 --> 00:41:04,562
have both been notified.

819
00:41:04,695 --> 00:41:05,062
Okay, okay.

820
00:41:05,162 --> 00:41:05,563
Okay.

821
00:41:13,571 --> 00:41:14,638
Xuemei told me.

822
00:41:15,005 --> 00:41:16,073
Is Hongxia's baby

823
00:41:16,373 --> 00:41:17,374
not doing very well?

824
00:41:18,476 --> 00:41:19,310
It's been almost two weeks since birth,

825
00:41:19,877 --> 00:41:21,212
but the ductus arteriosus is still open

826
00:41:21,612 --> 00:41:22,480
and quite large.

827
00:41:25,082 --> 00:41:26,183
It seems this baby

828
00:41:26,517 --> 00:41:27,518
isn't as fortunate

829
00:41:27,518 --> 00:41:28,352
as Xuemei's son.

830
00:41:30,287 --> 00:41:31,555
The ductus arteriosus is a blood vessel

831
00:41:31,555 --> 00:41:32,490
between the aorta

832
00:41:32,523 --> 00:41:33,324
and the pulmonary artery.

833
00:41:33,891 --> 00:41:34,625
While the baby is

834
00:41:34,625 --> 00:41:35,626
still in the womb,

835
00:41:35,693 --> 00:41:37,094
this vessel remains open.

836
00:41:37,328 --> 00:41:38,095
In full-term infants,

837
00:41:38,162 --> 00:41:39,263
within two weeks after birth,

838
00:41:39,430 --> 00:41:39,964
this vessel

839
00:41:39,997 --> 00:41:41,198
usually closes on its own.

840
00:41:41,665 --> 00:41:42,233
But in some

841
00:41:42,333 --> 00:41:43,534
premature infants,

842
00:41:43,801 --> 00:41:45,035
closure of this vessel

843
00:41:45,069 --> 00:41:45,636
may be delayed

844
00:41:45,803 --> 00:41:46,570
or may even

845
00:41:46,637 --> 00:41:47,605
fail to occur naturally.

846
00:41:48,505 --> 00:41:49,507
That's your baby's situation.

847
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:50,040
That's exactly what's happening.

848
00:41:51,008 --> 00:41:51,642
Then...

849
00:41:52,376 --> 00:41:53,444
what happens if it doesn't close?

850
00:41:53,944 --> 00:41:55,145
If it remains open,

851
00:41:55,246 --> 00:41:56,347
it can lead to a series of complications:

852
00:41:56,914 --> 00:41:58,315
bronchopulmonary dysplasia,

853
00:41:58,649 --> 00:41:59,650
necrotizing enterocolitis,

854
00:41:59,884 --> 00:42:00,885
changes in kidney function,

855
00:42:01,318 --> 00:42:02,953
and even intracranial hemorrhage.

856
00:42:04,889 --> 00:42:06,423
After consulting with Cardiology,

857
00:42:06,423 --> 00:42:07,424
our recommendation

858
00:42:07,892 --> 00:42:10,227
is to begin with conservative medical treatment.

859
00:42:10,528 --> 00:42:11,161
We hope

860
00:42:11,295 --> 00:42:12,630
the diameter of the ductus arteriosus

861
00:42:12,763 --> 00:42:14,365
will decrease or close.

862
00:42:17,935 --> 00:42:19,770
Some babies respond very well to medication

863
00:42:19,904 --> 00:42:21,472
and have a good prognosis.

864
00:42:22,039 --> 00:42:23,307
Let's observe for two weeks first.

865
00:42:37,154 --> 00:42:37,454
Hello?

866
00:42:37,922 --> 00:42:38,556
Hello, Director.

867
00:42:38,856 --> 00:42:39,890
Are you free right now?

868
00:42:40,357 --> 00:42:41,492
I just finished surgery. What's wrong?

869
00:42:41,892 --> 00:42:42,426
I have a patient

870
00:42:42,493 --> 00:42:43,561
with pulmonary hypertension.

871
00:42:43,994 --> 00:42:45,129
The case is unusual:

872
00:42:45,229 --> 00:42:46,163
a 1.5-centimeter ventricular septal defect

873
00:42:46,330 --> 00:42:47,197
with bidirectional shunting.

874
00:42:47,631 --> 00:42:49,466
The patient has a clear wish for surgery.

875
00:42:49,733 --> 00:42:50,935
Could you come take a look?

876
00:42:50,935 --> 00:42:51,435
Right now?

877
00:42:52,236 --> 00:42:53,070
Consultation Room 2.

878
00:42:53,637 --> 00:42:54,838
All right. I'm on my way.

879
00:42:55,439 --> 00:42:56,206
Ask Director Lin too.

880
00:42:56,407 --> 00:42:57,441
Have him come if he's free.
